<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 6:13PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Pittsburg County through 715 PM CDT...
At 611 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Horntown, moving south at 25 mph. Large hail is expected to fall
over Hughes County.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kiowa...                          Ashland...
Haywood...                        Scipio...
Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
